sentence.text: The positive regulation of cell-matrix adhesionty acid (FA) composition of protein phosphorylation blood cell (RBC) membrane phospholipids of cancer patients can reflect tumor status, dietary intakes, and cancer muscle organ development or therapy.

The adjusted Analysis of Covariance Test (ANCOVA) model revealed cancer patients to have a lower relative percentage of saturated positive regulation of cell-matrix adhesionty acids (SFA) (C16:0 (5.7%); C18:0 (15.9%)), and higher monounsaturated fatty acids (MUFA) (9c-C18:1 (12.9%) and 11c-C18:1 (54.5%)), compaprotein phosphorylation to controls.
